Male lectotype
. Measurements. Eye: 1.12 ; cl: 0.45 ; c-a: 0.61 ; c-o: 0.79 ; mhl: 1.56 ; c- e: 0.2 ; mhw: 1.75 ; F 4 : 0.22 ; mml: 0.08 ; abl: 6.16 . ( 1 ) Head. Wider than long. Supraclypeal area only weakly convex, its lateral portions with same curvature as adjacent paraocular surface. ( 2 ) Antennae. Flagellomeres II to XI subequal in length; on the anterior surface short pubescence restricted to basal and apical one-thirds of the flagellomeres, leaving a small glabrous area in the middle of each flagellomere; posterior surface of flagellomeres II to VII only weakly depressed in relation to anterior surface. ( 3 ) Mesoscutum. Outline, in dorsal view, of lateral half of projecting anterior border rounded. ( 4 ) Mesepisternum. Area below scrobal groove punctured, not rugulose. ( 5 ) Metapostnotum. Basal sulcus with few complete transverse carinae. ( 6 ) Propodeum. Punctation on dorso-lateral area dense, punctures about one-half puncture diameter apart. ( 7 ) Fore leg trochanter without dorsal hook, hook of mid leg trochanter short, about two-fifth trochanter width. ( 8 ) Metasoma. Disc of S 4 with central patch of erect setae and few lateral hairs (as in
Fig. 15
). ( 9 ) Genitalia. Not dissected (see
Figs. 22 and 23
). ( 10 ) Body color. Metallic green with mandibles, labrum, clypeal apex, femora, tibiae and tarsi yellow.
